    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead-big">We offer three individual short courses in the area of film and screen*. If you have successfully completed all three short courses, you will be eligible to graduate with a PgCert in Film and Screen Education</span>.</p>
<p>These courses are primarily for primary, secondary, and special school teachers in Scotland, though anyone who works regularly in educational settings is welcome to apply.</p>
<p>Please note that you cannot apply for the PgCert at the initial stage of application. Instead, you apply each short course individually and they must be taken in sequential order.</p>
<p>The three short courses are: (1) <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/70497527720b4284b1982bb10ce62975}" title="Introduction to Film Education">Introduction to Film Education</a>; (2) <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/29d17d8cddd34ab99c6cd46383139b86}" title="Filmmaking in the Classroom" data-anchor="#">Filmmaking in the Classroom*</a>; (3) <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/eccc19599eb344229dcbb2930419f636}" title="Professional Practice in Screen Education" data-anchor="#">Professional Practice in Film* Education </a></p>
<p>*The short courses marked * and the PgCert are still subject to validation. Updates will be posted here when available.</p>]]></Value>
    </introduction>
